ham and mother of Isaac. According to the Book of Genesis, she was originally called <i>Sarai</i> (possibly meaning ‘contentious’ in Hebrew), but had her name changed by God to the more auspicious <i>Sarah</i> ‘princess’ in token of a greater blessing (Genesis 17:15, ‘And God said unto Abraham, As for Sarai thy wife, thou shalt not call her name Sarai, but Sarah shall her name be’). This has been one of the most enduringly popular girls' names."],"variants":[{"name":"Sara","meanings":["Variant of   Sarah .  This is the form used in the Greek of the New Testament (Hebrews 11:11)."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Sarah Draper was born in 1135, in Loddon, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 2 sons with Sir Roger Hale."},"et":{"1135–":"1135–Surnud","1130–1190":"1130–1190","1155–Male":"1155–Surnud","1160–Male":"1160–Surnud","1135–Female":"1135–Surnud","1190":"1190","about 1160":"umbes 1160","1135":"1135","1155":"1155","1130":"1130","1160":"1160","Hales, Norfolk, England":"Hales, Norfolk, England","Loddon, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Loddon, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1135–":"1135–Kuollut","1130–1190":"1130–1190","1155–Male":"1155–Kuollut","1160–Male":"1160–Kuollut","1135–Female":"1135–Kuollut","1190":"1190","about 1160":"noin 1160","1135":"1135","1155":"1155","1130":"1130","1160":"1160","Hales, Norfolk, England":"Hales, Norfolk, England","Loddon, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Loddon, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1135–":"1135–Décédée","1130–1190":"1130–1190","1155–Male":"1155–Décédé","1160–Male":"1160–Décédé","1135–Female":"1135–Décédée","1190":"1190","about 1160":"environ 1160","1135":"1135","1155":"1155","1130":"1130","1160":"1160","Hales, Norfolk, England":"Hales, Norfolk, Angleterre","Loddon, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Loddon, Norfolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Sarah Drape